        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('MS Windows 95'); ?>
        <p><strong>Windows 95</strong> is a graphical user interface-based operating system. It was released on 24 August 1995 by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft', 'C'); ?>. During development, it was referred to as <strong>Windows 4.0</strong> or by the internal codename "<strong><em>Chicago</em></strong>".</p>
        <p>Windows 95 integrated Microsoft's formerly separate <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('MS-DOS', 'DOS'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows', 'OS'); ?> products. It featured significant improvements over its predecessor, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows 3', 'WIN'); ?>, most notably in the Graphical User Interface (<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('GUI', 'IT'); ?>) and in its relatively simplified "<em>plug-n-play</em>" features. There were also major changes made at lower levels of the operating system, such as moving from a mainly <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('16-bit', 'IT'); ?> architecture to a pre-emptively multitasked <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('32-bit', 'IT'); ?> architecture.</p>
        <p>Some three years after its introduction, Windows 95 was succeeded by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows 98', 'WIN'); ?>. Support for Windows 95 ended on 31 December 2001.</p>
